christians have you had something happen in your life that can only be explained as god's doing for example i was an athlete in college and was going to try out for my basketball team i went out and bought a new pair of nike bball shoes called flight those numbers spell nike on the phone well i ended up blowing out my knee ruining the ligaments and cartilage and basically ending any hopes of playing i was devestated i couldn't even look at those basketball shoes without feeling pain and bitterness but still prayed for god's will after college i was feeling very low had to work some menial job and basically felt like my prayers were going unanswered a buddy of mine wanted to share a bedroom and said he found an apartment and when i went to check it out the address was i kind of got the chills but kept praying one more i took a job at a place marriott dr and at a time i again was feeling abandoned by god my parents invited me to go to austin tx for a getaway the room at the marriott hotel i listen to every word god says i love it when god shows us how much he cares about us you see in all the traveling and places you went you may have somewhere along the line turned the heart of someone in just some small word you said to be the next billy graham or chuck swindol or maybe the parents of some man or woman of god gods word never returns void though we sometimes feel let down when we get to heaven and realize who we touched with our lives while we thought it was all unfair it will be worth it all One Tree Hill (TV series) Fancy Crane Miss Saigon Humphrey Bogart Friends Paul Is Dead Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Ocean's Twelve Basketball Blood on the Tracks Church of Christ, Scientist Past teachings of Prem Rawat The Catcher in the Rye Spiritism Oh My Goddess! EastEnders Shaggy dog story Angel Good Times Cliff Richard Charmed Christian eschatology Jon Secada Sabbath God and gender Infidels John Howard Yoder Rule of St Benedict The Inside Volleyball Knots L